07/02/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The country's most famous director, Danis Tanovic, whose "No Man's Land" won an Oscar for best foreign language film in 2002, announced on Wednesday (February 6th) that he plans to form a new political party, whose main goal would be to fight widespread corruption and improve the public's quality of life. The party plans to compete in the October local elections. (AFP, Fena, RTRS, Dnevni Avaz - 06/02/08)
